'''''Galaxy of Fear: Eaten Alive''''' is a [[Star Wars Legends|''Star Wars'' Legends]] junior novel written by [[John Whitman]]. It is the first volume of the ''[[Star Wars: Galaxy of Fear]]'' series, and it was first published by [[Bantam Spectra|Bantam Skylark]] in [[January]] [[1997]]. A sequel, ''[[Galaxy of Fear: City of the Dead]]'', was published later that year.

==Publisher's summary==
''Vanished?''

''D'vouran seems like a normal enough planet. The friendly locals welcome Tash, Zak, and their uncle Hoole with open arms.''

''But Tash has a bad feeling about this place.''

''There's a madman running around the streets shouting that people are disappearing. He's saying they've just vanished into thin air.''

''Tash knows that's impossible. But something is really wrong on D'vouran. Will she find the courage to trust her gut instincts&hellip;before it's too late?''

==Plot summary==
[[Tash Arranda/Legends|Tash]] and [[Zak Arranda/Legends|Zak Arranda]] are preteen siblings whose [[Parent/Legends|parents]] were [[Death/Legends|killed]] when the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] destroyed their home [[Planet/Legends|planet]] of [[Alderaan/Legends|Alderaan]]. With nowhere else to go, they began to travel with their [[Mammon Hoole|Uncle Hoole]], a mysterious [[Changeling/Legends|shape-shifting]] [[Shi'ido]] who studies different [[Species/Legends|species]] on many planets. They live with him on his [[Starship/Legends|starship]], the ''[[Lightrunner]]'', and learn from their new caretaker [[Droid/Legends|droid]], [[DV-9]]. When they travel to the mysterious planet of [[D'vouran]], they are pulled out of [[Hyperspace/Legends|hyperspace]], seemingly too soon, by the planet's gravity, and crash land at the [[D'vouran spaceport|spaceport]]. Though Tash feels bad things about the planet, the [[Enzeen]], the [[Alien/Legends|alien]] race who live on the planet, are more than happy to help out with anything they need while on the planet. D'vouran has become a tourist destination and the Enzeen hope to bring more people to live on the planet. 

When [[Chood]], the Enzeen who personally helps the family, brings them to an inn to find help in repairing the [[Engine/Legends|engine]], they are attacked and the [[Youngling/Legends|children]] taken captive by the forces of [[Smada|Smada the Hutt]], who demands Hoole's service. With help from the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebels]] who are also investigating the planet, Smada's forces release the children. Outside of the inn, they meet [[Kevreb Bebo]], a disgraced [[Pilot/Legends|pilot]] who tries to warn the people staying on planet that people are disappearing. When their Uncle Hoole leaves them with Chood while he is studying, Tash sees an alien creature standing over [[Sleep/Legends|sleeping]] Zak. Waking him, they run to [[City/Legends|town]] to warn the others, only to find that no one is chasing them. After Hoole speaks to them, Tash stops worrying about the planet and who is chasing them.

The next [[Standard day/Legends|day]], Zak, while alone, is attacked by Smada's forces. Bebo is there also, and manages to evade all their [[Laser/Legends|laser]] shots at him. Hoole is eventually able to stop Smada, but Tash convinces him to let her speak with Bebo. He brings her, accompanied by DV-9, to a [[Cave/Legends|cave]], where he shows her a [[Laboratory/Legends|laboratory]] which had long ago been abandoned. He shows her a seemingly bottomless pit, which she feels there is something wrong with, and he shows her his [[D'vouran amulet|medallion]], a device which apparently keeps him safe from the disappearances. Believing him, she tries to return to the town. He gives her his medallion, but, after she has gone, he is killed by one of Smada's guards. As she returns to town, she is attacked by the Enzeen, who have become [[Parasite/Legends|parasitic]] monsters, but manages to escape when an [[Groundquake/Legends|earthquake]] shakes the ground. Back at town, however, everyone is missing, and she goes to [[Smada's stronghold|Smada's fortress]], thinking he has done something. 

There she finds Zak in [[Prison/Legends|captivity]]. With DV-9's help, they escape Smada's fortress, but are recaptured easily. However, now outside the fortress, Smada, his guards, and the children are attacked by the Enzeen and the planet, as holes begin to open up and take people into the planet. Smada, on his [[Hoversled/Legends|repulsor sled]], and the children, protected by the medallion, are kept safe, but are brought by the Enzeen to the heart of the planet, the pit Bebo showed Tash. There it is revealed that the planet is [[Living Force/Legends|alive]] and needs nourishment, and the Enzeen get their own nourishment from the planet while attracting more people to come. The medallion created a [[Force field/Legends|forcefield]] around the wearers that the planet couldn't absorb. When Hoole, who was disguised as an Enzeen, gets the medallion, he throws it into the pit, causing the planet to begin to erupt. Able to escape the pit, even as Smada falls in and is absorbed, they finally reach their ship. The ship, however, is unable to take off, as the planet has grabbed hold of it. Losing hope, the [[Millennium Falcon/Legends|''Millennium Falcon'']] comes to their rescue and, with deft flying by [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]], is finally able to escape the planet, which collapses on itself behind them.

==Development==
''Galaxy of Fear: Eaten Alive'' was developed in the spirit of [[Wikipedia:Goosebumps|''Goosebumps'']], a series of juvenile horror novels from author [[Wikipedia:R. L. Stine|R. L. Stine]], and it was published in paperback by [[Bantam Spectra|Bantam Skylark]]. The novel has a holographic cover and was marketed as a one-time-only "Limited Collector's Edition."<ref name="Year by Year" />

==Continuity==
The [[2012]] reference book ''[[The Essential Reader's Companion]]'' dates the events of ''Galaxy of Fear: Eaten Alive'' to [[0 ABY/Legends|0 ABY]], placing the novel after the short story "[[Fair Prey]]" ([[2000]]) and before ''[[Galaxy of Fear: City of the Dead]]'' ([[1997]]).<ref name="Essential Reader's Companion" />

